2. NodePort
🔹 What is it?

Exposes service on a specific port of each node

🔹 Why?

To access application from outside cluster (basic way)

🔹 Where used?

Testing / development

🔹 How it works?
<NodeIP>:Port
🎤 Interview Answer

“NodePort exposes the application on a port of each node, allowing external access using node IP and port.”
